<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1239] Builders: calls to owner methods from within nested closures lead to markup instead of method calling</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1239</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This seems similar to a problem I experience with SwingBuilder.. where&lt;br/&gt;
a change made it impossible to call methods from inside the builder.&lt;br/&gt;
To fix it i had to do something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def self = this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;swing {&lt;br/&gt;
      button(action:&lt;/p&gt;
{ self.someMethod() }
&lt;p&gt; )&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;void someMethod() {&lt;br/&gt;
 // the method&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note the above is just psuedo code from memory but the problems seem similar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Graeme&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On 11/02/06, Dierk Koenig &amp;lt;dierk.koenig@canoo.com&amp;gt; wrote:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Hi,&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; the following Groovlet runs fine&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ----&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; html.html{&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     head &lt;/p&gt;
{
&amp;gt;         title &apos;Groovlet Demonstrator&apos;
&amp;gt;     }&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     content()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; }&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; void content() {
&amp;gt;     html.body &apos;Welcome&apos;
&amp;gt; }&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ----&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; This fails:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ----&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; html.html{&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     head {&amp;gt;         title &apos;Groovlet Demonstrator&apos;&amp;gt;     }
&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;     p &lt;/p&gt;
{ content() }
&lt;p&gt; // &amp;lt;- mind the p{}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; }&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; void content() &lt;/p&gt;
{
&amp;gt;     html.body &apos;Welcome&apos;
&amp;gt; }
&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; ----&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; It produces:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ----&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;   &amp;lt;head&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     &amp;lt;title&amp;gt;Groovlet Demonstrator&amp;lt;/title&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;   &amp;lt;/head&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;   &amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     &amp;lt;content /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;   &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ----&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Logs are empty.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Has anybody an idea? Has it anything to do with the latest&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; changes to Closures?&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; cheers&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Mittie&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
